{
  "stem": "1975.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember we used to have in our house an old Marconi, Italian.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in some occasions, based on the time difference, I used to listen to-- certain times, we used to catch the United States of America, which was quite interesting.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "As time rolled, we start finding out many things, because we have had some refugees from Czechoslovakia who came to us.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, later we had also some Polish refugees who fought the-- the Germans.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But that was at a later date.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we tried to help the Jewish refugees that came from Czechoslovakia, because they came illegally, and we tried to provide them shelter and tried to make their stay legal.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was not easy, but we were able to do that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were actually, for some reason, we haven't been concerned, because we felt that Lithuania is a safe place.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's a democratic country.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we felt that-- we truthfully were shortsighted.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't realize what actually-- what kind of storm is coming against us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But especially when we had this opportunity to meet those who escaped from Czechoslovakia, this was a-- and we listened to their stories and to the stories of horror, we start thinking that times might be not as good in the future as they were, as we had them.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But still, we were entrenched in our country.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We have not-- never, we never had a thought that something terrible can happen to us.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had many, many, many people-- I mean, many.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were a number of people who used to emigrate.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We used to travel to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had some friends who went to Palestine at that time because the spirit of the Jewish, the Zionist movement was very strong in our city.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
